Police have launched a murder investigation following a second alleged killing at London care homes in the past 24 hours. A 34-year-old man was declared dead at the scene after emergency services were called to an address in Newham, east London, at 3:45am. Metropolitan Police say a 21-year-old man has been arrested on suspicion of murder. In the other incident, a 60-year-old man was allegedly killed at a different adult care home in Hayes just before midnight yesterday, My London reports. Regarding the Newham tragedy, a spokesman for Met Police said: "An investigation has been launched by detectives from the Met’s Specialist Crime Command who are in the process of informing the man’s next of kin. "A post-mortem examination is due to be held at East Ham Mortuary on Wednesday, January 4."   The force has not said the two investigations are linked. A 44-year-old man, who was also a resident in the Hayes care home, was arrested on suspicion of murder. Both investigations continue in the capital. We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. Please check back regularly for updates on this developing story. Get email updates on the day’s biggest stories straight to your inbox by signing up for our newsletters. Get all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you by following Daily Express every time you see our name. Follow Daily Express on Google News. Follow Daily Express on Apple News - available on Apple devices. Follow Daily Express on Flipboard. You can sign up for Twitter alerts for breaking news and follow us, for all the latest updates.